  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 345.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there-- these flags had been made by the women of the congregation, and some of them were really beautiful.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And always.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Those two kids got the best flags, because they lived right there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] The school and the teacher's home and the synagogue was in one complex.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And so naturally, they were there first and they always got the best flags.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But they were really very nice children.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Their names were Edis and Walter.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And one other thing about them, when I came to Rheydt the last days of my stay in Germany to say goodbye to my friends, because I had been living in Bonn, I went to visit them also.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we were playing cards.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Walter, the older of the two children-- perhaps at that time, he might have been already 13 or 14 years old, and I guess his sister was 12.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He said while he was-- he showed me how to shuffle cards the way they do in a casino, you know?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They kind of-- you can kind of flip them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And while he was doing that, he said, you know, Hitler said by 1941 there wouldn't be a Jew alive in Germany.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, I do those-- I still flip the cards that way.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And every time I do it, I think of him and what he said.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] When we were invited back to Germany in 1989, to Rheydt, there was a-- a display in a museum of the history of the Jews of the area and their contribution to the area.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there was a picture of the teacher, of Max Heiman.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
